Object TDmxEditBuf
==================

    TDmxEditBuf is a descendant of TDmxEditor that uses a circular buffer
    (referred to as "slots") to edit data from a source other than in RAM.

    It retrieves each record individually when accessed.  The buffer is
    only used for quick page draws.

    This object can be found in unit tvDMXBUF.  It uses several abstract
    methods and must not be instantiated as is.  Objects TDmxStreamBuf and
    TDmxExpBuf are usable descendants that work with streams.

    Descendants MUST override methods SeekRec(), ReadRec() and WriteRec().
    Most descendants may also require overiding methods RecordLimit() and
    SeekEnd().  See object TDmxEditRecBuf for a derivative that employs
    NextRec() and PrevRec() functions instead of SeekRec().

    The SeekRec() and RecordLimit() methods used INTEGERs with tvDMX
    versions prior to 2.1.  LONGINTs are used now, but the new paging
    scheme is still incomplete.


FIELDS
------

  Appending	:  boolean;

	Indicates that the current record will be a new record.


  Expandable	:  boolean;

	TRUE if new records can be appended to this data window.


  KeyAltered	:  boolean;

	Indicates that a key field was altered so that the circular
	buffer will be refreshed after the current record is entered.


  KeyFields	:  set of byte;

	Set of numbers that represents which fields could cause an index
	file to reposition a record if the key field was altered.  This
	value is initialized as [] by default, and is not changed by any
	of the objects in this unit.  Descendants that use keyed files
	may alter this value.


  NumSlots	:  integer;

	Total number of record storage slots in the buffer.


  RowSlot	:  PRowSlots;

	A pointer to the circular buffer that is allocated during this
	object's construction.


  StepMode	:  boolean;

	Set during initialization if this data window uses Next() and
	Previous() methods to scan forward or backward.  This is set
	FALSE, and it can only be used for TDmxEditRecBuf descendants.


METHODS
-------

  constructor Load (var S : TStream);

    Calls its descendant and then reads the object's fields.


  func  DataAt (RecNum : integer)  : pointer;
	VIRTUAL;

    Returns a pointer to the given data record in buffer RowSlot^
    --using the ReadRec() function.


  proc  DeleteRec;
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract method to delete the current record.  The default
    method sets RecordAltered to TRUE, to ensure that the record is
    cleared.  Descendants should override this method if the record is
    being physically deleted from the database.


  proc  DoneStruct;
	VIRTUAL;

    Frees the memory allocated for the buffer RowSlot and then calls
    its ancestor.


  func  ErrorFunc : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method to handle I/O errors.  This method should take care
    of the error and return TRUE if the error should be ignored or FALSE
    if the failed operation should be retried.
    The default method uses Turbo Vision's SystemError() function to
    give the user the option of repeating the operation.


  proc  EvaluateField;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called AFTER each FIELD is edited.
    Sets KeyAltered to TRUE if a change was made and the current field
    is a key field  Then calls TDmxEditor.EvaluateRecord().


  proc  EvaluateRecord;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called AFTER each RECORD is edited.
    Calls WriteRec() to write the record to the stream if the record
    was altered.  Then calls TDmxEditor.EvaluateRecord().


  proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls ResetSlots() to reset the RowSlot buffer when a cmDMX_Draw
    or cmDMX_DrawData command is received.


  proc  InitStruct (var ATemplate );
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditor.InitStruct() to initialize the field-descriptor
    chain and then calls MakeSlots().


  proc  LoadStruct (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditor.LoadStruct() to initialize the field-descriptor
    chain and then calls MakeSlots().


  proc  MakeSlots;

    Allocates memory for the RowSlot buffer.


  func  ReadRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method called by DataAt() to retrieve a record.
    This function must read a record from the current record position
    and return TRUE if the operation succeeded or FALSE if it failed.
    It is the programmer's responsibility to retain the error code for
    use by the ErrorFunc() method.


  func  RecordLimit : longint;
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract method that returns the number of records in the
    database.  This method should always be overridden to work with a
    specific database technique, but a default method is provided that
    returns the value of (DataBlockSize div RecordSize).


  proc  ResetSize;

    Compares RecordLimit() to the current size of the table and resets
    DataBlockSize and the Limit.X if necessary.
    Used only for expandable databases.


  proc  ResetSlots;

    Resets the circular buffer.


  func  SeekEnd : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract virtual method to seek to the end of the database.
    This is only used for expandable databases.
    It must return a value of TRUE if the operation succeeded or FALSE
    if the operation failed.  It is the programmer's responsibility to
    retain the error code for use by the ErrorFunc() method.


  func  SeekRec (RecNum : longint) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method to seek to the given record position.  It is
    called before reading or writing a record.  It must return a value of
    TRUE if the operation succeeded or FALSE if the operation failed.
    It is the programmer's responsibility to retain the error code for use
    by the ErrorFunc() method.


  proc  SetState (AState : word; Enable : boolean);
	VIRTUAL;

    If Expandable is TRUE then it checks if the size of the data table
    has changed when the view becomes reselected.


  proc  SetUpRecord;
	VIRTUAL;

    Called BEFORE each RECORD is edited.
    Clears the buffer for the current record's slot position to ensure
    that the data will be recent, and then calls its anscestor.


  proc  Store (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls its descendant and then writes the object's fields.


  func  WriteRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method called by EvaluateRecord() to store a record.
    This function must write a record to the current record position and
    return TRUE if the operation succeeded or FALSE if it failed.
    It is the programmer's responsibility to retain the error code for use
    by the ErrorFunc() method.


  proc  ZeroizeField (Whole : boolean; Field : pDMXfieldrec);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditor.EvaluateRecord() and then sets KeyAltered to TRUE if
    the current field is a key field.

Object TDmxStreamBuf
====================

    TDmxStreamBuf is a descendant of TDmxEditBuf to edit data from a stream.
    This stream type can be any derivation of TStream.

    The stream must already be open and its initialization and finalization
    must be handled outside of tvDMX.  (This way, you can have other windows
    and objects refer to this same stream.)

    A file header will be provided for if PrefixSize is set to the size
    of the header.  This should be done by a descendant of InitData().

    Although this was created for editing data files, it should be usable
    with any TStream derivative.  This object can be found in unit tvDMXBUF.


FIELDS
------

  Prefix	:  pointer;

	Pointer to a file prefix, or header, if one exists.  Many file
	formats (eg: dBASE) use a file prefix with information about the
	record structure.  This object provides only for the the space
	used by the prefix when seeking to a specific record.
	It would be the responsibility of its descendants to keep a file
	prefix updated.


  PrefixSize	:  integer;

	The size of a file header/prefix.


METHODS
-------

  func  ErrorFunc : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This method resets the stream error and then calls its ancestor.


  proc  LoadStruct (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditBuf.LoadStruct() and then reads the PrefixSize field.


  func  ReadRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This function reads RecordSize number of bytes from the stream.
    (RecordSize is a field inherited from TDmxScroller.)


  func  RecordLimit : integer;
	VIRTUAL;

    Returns the number of records in the database, as determined by
    the file size minus PrefixSize.


  func  SeekRec (RecNum : longint) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Seeks to the given record position --taking PrefixSize into account.


  func  SeekEnd : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Seeks to the end of the database.


  proc  StoreStruct (var S : TStream);
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditBuf.StoreStruct() and then writes the PrefixSize field.


  func  WriteRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This function writes RecordSize number of bytes to the stream.
    (RecordSize is an inherited field.)

Object TDmxExpBuf
=================

    TDmxExpBuf is a descendant of TDmxStreamBuf that expands as records
    are added.  The stream must be initialized with an existing file, but
    the file's starting length can be zero.

    The BSize parameter (of the Init constructor) is used to set the
    PrefixSize variable.  The file size determines the database size.
    This object can be found in unit tvDMXBUF.PAS.

    See program file FILESHOP.PAS for an example of TDmxExpBuf usage.

    This derivative has no special fields and only one method.


METHODS
-------

  proc  InitData (var AData );
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxStreamBuf.InitData() and then it must correct for the
    initialization of DataBlockSize as the size of the Prefix:
    Expandable is set to TRUE;  PrefixSize is set to DataBlockSize;
    and DataBlockSize is reset by calling TDmxEditBuf.ResetSize().

Object TDmxEditRecBuf
=====================

    TDmxEditRecBuf is a descendant of TDmxEditBuf to access records with
    virtual methods that are adapted from database tools.  The SeekRec()
    function was overridden to change find records using the FirstRec(),
    LastRec(), NextRec() and PrevRec() abstract methods.

    The following methods must be overridden to create usable descendant
    objects:  AppendRec(), FirstRec(), LastRec(), NextRec(), PrevRec() and
    UpdateRec().  Start and end of database errors that may occur when
    editing indexed databases must be handled by a descendant ErrorFunc()
    method.

    This object can be found in unit tvDMXBUF.


METHODS
-------

  func  AppendRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This abstract method should append the current record with RecData
    and return TRUE if there is no error.


  func  FirstRec : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Pseudo-abstract method to seek to the first record position.
    The default method repeats PrevRec() until it receives an error.
    (The error is ignored, and the function always returns TRUE.)
    It should be overridden with a more efficient method whenever
    possible to seek directly to the first record, and return TRUE if
    there is no error.


  proc  InitData (var AData );
	VIRTUAL;

    Calls TDmxEditBuf.InitData() and then sets StepMode to TRUE.


  func  LastRec : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method to seek to the last record position.
    This method should be overridden to seek to the last record
    position, and it should return TRUE if there is no error.


  func  NextRec : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method to seek to the next record position.
    This method should be overridden to seek to the next record
    position, and it should return TRUE if there is no error.


  func  PrevRec : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Abstract virtual method to seek to the previous record position.
    This method should be overridden to seek to the previous record
    position, and it should return TRUE if there is no error.


  func  SeekEnd : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This method satisfies the requirement for seeking to new records
    by returning TRUE, and doing nothing else.


  func  SeekRec (RecNum : longint) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This method uses FirstRec(), NextRec(), and PrevRec() to seek to a
    record.  It returns TRUE if there was no error.


  func  UpdateRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    This abstract method should update the current record with RecData
    and return TRUE if there is no error.


  func  WriteRec (var RecData ) : boolean;
	VIRTUAL;

    Virtual method to write a record.
    This method calls AppendRec() or UpdateRec(), depending upon the
    boolean field Appending.

  proc  ZeroizeRecord;
	VIRTUAL;

    If Appending is set TRUE then it calls its anscestor to clear the
    current record.  If not Appending then it prompts the user to confirm
    that deleting the record is desired.


